{"ID":270256, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"256\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs255.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs257.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 256<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">keeping all the commandments of God.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> But we cannot keep all the commandments without first\n  knowing them,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and we cannot expect to know all, or more than we now know unless we comply<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span>\n  with or keep those we have already received. That which is wrong under one circumstance, may be,\n  and often is, right under another.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">God said, &ldquo;Thou shalt not kill;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> at another time He said, &ldquo;Thou shalt utterly destroy.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> This is\n  the principle on which the government of heaven is conducted&mdash;by revelation adapted to the\n  circumstances in which the children of the kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> are placed. Whatever God requires is right,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span>\n  no matter what it is, although we may not see the reason<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> thereof till long after the events transpire.\n  If we seek first the kingdom of God, all good things will be added.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> So with Solomon: first he asked\n  wisdom,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and God gave it him, and with it every desire of his heart,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> even things which might be\n  considered abominable<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> to all who understand the order of heaven<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> only in part,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> but which in\n  reality were right because God gave and sanctioned by special revelation.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">A parent may whip a child,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and justly, too, because he stole an apple; whereas if the child had\n  asked for the apple, and the parent had given it, the child would have eaten it with a better appetite;\n  there would have been no stripes; all the pleasure of the apple would have been secured, all the\n  misery of stealing lost.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Every Gift from God Is Just<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">This principle will justly apply to all of God&rsquo;s dealings with His children. Everything that God\n  gives us is lawful and right; and it is proper that we should enjoy His gifts and blessings whenever\n  and wherever He is disposed to bestow; but if we should seize upon those same blessings<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and\n  enjoyments without law, without revelation, without commandment, those blessings and enjoyments\n  would prove cursings and vexations<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> in the end, and we should have to lie down in sorrow<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> and\n  wailings of everlasting regret. But in obedience there is joy<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and peace unspotted, unalloyed; and\n  as God has designed our happiness<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span>&mdash;and the happiness of all His creatures,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> he never has&mdash;He\n  never will institute an ordinance<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> or give a commandment to His people that is not calculated in its\n  nature to promote that happiness which He has designed, and which will not end<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111530\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111530)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111530)\">Mosiah 2:41<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108355\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108355)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108355)\">Mark 10:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111583\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111583)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111583)\">Mosiah 6:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115027\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115027)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115027)\">D&amp;C 93:28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116964\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116964)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116964)\">Abr. 1:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106167\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106167)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106167)\">Ex. 20:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116412\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116412)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116412)\">D&amp;C 132:36<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106177\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106177)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106177)\">Ex. 22:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106281\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106281)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106281)\">Deut. 7:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106393\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106393)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106393)\">1 Sam. 15:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108029\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108029)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108029)\">Matt. 13:38<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113711\